-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Close Brothers, Barclays
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 01:33AM EDT
-- None



Aug 28 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Close Brothers and Barclays, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Financials: Barclays starts Close Brothers, Paragon with overweight [ID:nWNAB04MXA]* Barclays <BARC.L>: Jefferies raises target price to 331p from 325p; rating buy Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Barclays <BARC.L>: Jefferies raises target price to 331p from 325p; rating buy * Bureau Veritas <BVI.PA>: Jefferies cuts target price to 23 euros from 25 euros; rating buy * Bureau Veritas <BVI.PA>: Barclays cuts target to 19.50 euros from 20.50 euros; underweight * Close Brothers Group <CBRO.L>: Barclays starts with overweight; price target 1500p * Credit Agricole <CAGR.PA>: Jefferies ups target to 14.50 euros from 13.50 euros; buy * Evraz <EVRE.L>: Jefferies raises price target to 100p from 90p; rating hold * OMV AG <OMVV.VI>: Jefferies starts with hold; price target euros 27 * Paragon Group <PARA.L>: Barclays starts with overweight; price target 410p